This is part of VICE Sports' 2016 NHL preview coverage. You can read all our stories here.

Usually when a team is coming off a disastrous season in which it missed the playoffs by a mile, expectations are tempered, but that isn't really the case for the 2016-17 edition of the Montreal Canadiens. With the nature of last season's struggles being mostly due to injuries—specifically Carey Price missing all but 12 games—expectations were already going to be high, anyway.
